    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>
                    <sic>Sanfrancisco</sic>
                </placeName>
                <date>March 30th 1864</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Herewith I<lb/> send you a copy of my Discourses. I shall<lb/> be
                happy to have you review it, as I know<lb/> it will be ably and impartially done. I
                would<lb/> willingly have sent you some copies for sale, but<lb/> the price is too
                high. I published 1500 copies<lb/> which cost me <hi rend="underline">700 dollars
                    in-Gold</hi>. They are<lb/> sold here for 1 Dollar pr copy. If you should<lb/>
                think well of it and could affect a sale in the<lb/> states we might talk of your
                publishing them<lb/> yourself for the states. <hi rend="underline">I think I shall
                    sell one</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">thousand Copies here</hi>. The Book is well received<lb/> here,
                all the press have noticed it favorably except<lb/> the “<hi rend="underline"
                    >Gleaner</hi>” which no doubt you have seen<lb/> The “<hi rend="underline"
                    >Hebrew</hi>” I think will succeed. The Messenger<lb/> of <placeName>New
                    York</placeName> sympathizes with the “<hi rend="underline">Gleaner</hi>”<lb/>
                in consequence of the appearance of the “Hebrew”<lb/> which I consider out of place.
                What is your opinion?<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Frank</persName> of <placeName>New York</placeName> is here, and on his
                return<lb/> to <placeName>New York</placeName> wishes to publish my Class Book as
                the<lb/> whole Edition has been consumed. He will do so<lb/> in his own
                responsibility, as the price is too high here.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I suppose you have considered that I have<lb/> neglected in not writing to you the
                fact is that<lb/> very little has <sic>traspired</sic> here worth troubling<lb/>
                you. What has <sic>occured</sic> you can learn from<lb/> the “Hebrew” and “Gleaner”
                I do not write for the<lb/> Gleaner, but I do for the “<hi rend="underline"
                    >Hebrew</hi>” from which<lb/> you can copy the several items. I am anxious<lb/>
                to see the Hebrew succeed, although I am not<lb/> interested in the same from any
                pecuniary benefit<lb/> as the “Gleaner” would make you believe.<lb/> The fact is it
                is jealous and envious and<lb/> wishes to grasp every thing—and I do not
                endorse<lb/> such mercenary motives such does not form<lb/> any part of my
                character. And therefore I do<lb/> try and assist the “Hebrew” such a paper
                being<lb/> wanted in the <placeName>Pacific Coast</placeName>. A new society<lb/> is
                being formed here entitled “The Universal<lb/> Jewish Alliance” to cooperate with
                the Central<lb/> Committee in <placeName>Paris, France</placeName>. <sic>full</sic>
                particulars<lb/> you will find published in the “<hi rend="underline">Hebrew</hi>”
                so that<lb/> I need not trouble you with writing it now.<lb/> I have had but little
                success disposing<lb/> of your Books, I shall however immediately<lb/> after
                    <add>פסח</add> make up my account and forward<lb/> you what I have in hand, and
                my own <sic>indebtness</sic><lb/> for your publications. Your Occident I read
                with<lb/> pleasure, it is the only periodical among our people<lb/> which contains
                any thing worth reading.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>I hope I shall soon have the pleasure<lb/> of hearing from you</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In the hope that this will meet<lb/> you in health, happiness &amp;
                prosperity</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Believe me</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">H. A. Henry</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
